(2420, 15, '17 The assertion that conflict are processes that tend to degenerate from non-violent to violent and from crisis to full-scale war can be credited to ___________', 'Stagner Bright', 'Kriesbarg Dan', 'Quicy wright', 'Laue Mayor', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2421, 15, '18 Which of these parties or characters may not involve in conflict creation', 'Ethnic group', 'Religious group', 'Racial group', 'Minor group', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2422, 15, '19 One of the following proponents do not see anything wrong in conflict. He sees conflict as an instrument of change', 'Quincy', 'Kriesbarg', 'Rose', 'Laue', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2423, 15, '20 The principle of exogenous and endogenous conflict was postulated by __________________', 'Dahrendorf', 'Quincy wright', 'Max weber', 'Resort gurri', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2424, 15, '1 Some of the tribal conflict in Nigeria can be traced to ______________', 'ethnic stereotypes', 'resource control', 'uneven political appointment', 'terrorism', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2425, 15, '2 Which of the following is not a barrier to social perception____________', 'selective perception', 'first impression error', 'cognitive perception', 'self fulfilling prophesies', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2426, 15, '3 Which of these stages is characterized by the formation of enemy images', 'Improvement stage', 'Escalation stage', 'Violent stage', 'Transformation', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2427, 15, '4 At what stage of conflict situation will parties involved begin to experience gradual cessation of hostifity', 'Improvement stage', 'De-escalation stage', 'Esealation stage', 'Crisis stage', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2428, 15, '5 Which of these is not an indicator of impending conflict', 'Growing poverty', 'Unemployment', 'Inequality', 'Spiritualism', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2429, 15, '6 Going by the paper on Danida conference on Conflict Prevention and Peace Building in Africa, at what phase can a conflict be easily nipped in the bud', 'Latent', 'Manifest', 'Contained', 'Mitigated', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2430, 15, '7 Which of these is not a proposition on roles according to turner', 'Roles in relation to psychology', 'roles in societal setting', 'roles in organizational setting', 'roles as an interactive frame work', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2431, 15, '8 Some trade actors or network that may involve in causing or exacerbating conflict include those in ______________', 'aquatic industries', 'extractive industries', 'constructive industries', 'educative industries', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2432, 15, '9 Which of these communities do not see conflict as negative in their language', 'Russian', 'Chinese', 'German', 'Western', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2433, 15, '10 Conflict tends to evolve in a ___________ patterns', 'triangular', 'Polygonal', 'cyclical', 'Rectangular', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2434, 15, '11 Conflict was viewed as having a constructive contribution towards a healthy industrial order. This is according to _________________', 'Pluralist perspective', 'Structural-functional theory', 'Theory of structural balance', 'Singularist perspective', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2435, 15, '12 The theory which sees conflict as dysfunctional, abnormal and a disease which can be endemic to a society is called ______', 'The theory of structural balance', 'Structural-functional theory', 'Pluralist perspective theory', 'Max Weber theory', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2436, 15, '13 Going by the assumption on ethnicity and conflict __________ argued that ethnicity and nationalism are not given but are social and political construction', 'Thomson', 'Bamass', 'Toland', 'Novak', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2437, 15, '14 Ethnicity and nationalism are the creation of elites who draw upon distorted and fabricated materials from culture of the group to gain political and economics advantage. This position is an extracts from', 'Krugen, 1933', 'Quincy, 1934', 'Kriesbarg, 1973', 'Laue, 1990', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2438, 15, '15 The individualism in conflict transformation posited that " A collectivist society is __________ an individual society is ______', 'tighthy integrated and loosely integrated', 'upwardly transfomed and downwardly transformed', 'intrisicly formed and extrinsily formed', 'overtly planned and covertly planned', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2439, 15, '16 Conflict is related to meaning, meaning to knowledge and knowledge is rooted in __________', 'Philosophy', 'Culture', 'Ideas', 'Metaphysics', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2440, 15, '17 At what phase according to Bjon Mollar will conflicting parties express their demands and grieveances openly, but only by legal means', 'Escalation phase', 'Violent Phase', 'Manifest phase', 'Resolution phase', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2441, 15, '18 The phase of conflict that is characterised by direct physical attacks and confrontation leading to spilling of blood and loss of life is known as ___________', 'Escalation', 'Super violent', 'Violent', 'Hyper-escalation', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2442, 15, '19 At what definte phase will violence breed further violence producing an escalatory momentum', 'Mitigated phase', 'Contained phase', 'De-escalation phase', 'Escalation phase', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2443, 15, '20 At the point when conflicting parties have temporarily exhausted their supply of weaponry, leading to lower intensity is called __________', 'Latent Phase', 'Resolution phase', 'Contained phase', 'Mitigated Phase', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2444, 15, '1 Which of these best described the mitigated phase in conflict resolution?____________', 'Less violence and more political mobilization and negotiation', 'State of military inforvention', 'When mediation effort is at top gear', 'People promoting private agenda', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2445, 15, '2 The resolution phase is characterised by all these except_________________', 'Expression of grieveances and taking sides', 'Re-ordering of power relationship', 'Faciliting re- conciliation between opposing sides', 'Disarmament, demobilization, and re-integration', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2446, 15, '3 The two basic dimension of conflict handling styles are _______________', 'Assertiveness and cooprativeness', 'Avoiding and collaborating', 'Confronatation and dominating', 'Problem solving', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2447, 15, '4 The dimension of behaviour that can be used to explain or define conflict handing styles include all the following except ______', 'Collaborating', 'Accomodating', 'Compromising', 'Cohabitting', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2448, 15, '5 The process which involve monitoring, observing and recording the trend of change and continuity in the conflict process___________', 'Conflict charting', 'Conflict tracking', 'Conflict charting', 'Conflict supervision', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2449, 15, '6 A conflict handing style that is characterized as unassertive and cooperative is called _______', 'Cohasitting', 'Accomodating', 'Dominating', 'Resolving', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2450, 15, '7 When you are partially assertive and partially cooperative in a conflict handing process, it regarded as ____________', 'Dominating', 'Accomodating', 'Compromising', 'Avoiding', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2451, 15, '8 Which of these conflict handling styles can be grouped under the second model _______________', 'Collaborating/Accomodating', 'Confrontation/fighting', 'Cooperativeness/assertiveness', 'Improvement/escalation', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2452, 15, '9 In the second model, at what point will parties in conflict show respect for differences and look for ways to end problem_______', 'Problem solving', 'Discussion approach', 'Concession', 'Compromissing', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2453, 15, '10 The graphical representation of the conflict in which of the conflicting parties are placed in relation to the situation on ground is called ________', 'Conflict mapping', 'Conflict charting', 'Conflict tracking', 'Conflict geography', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2454, 15, '11 ________ is the critical review interpretation and explanation of what is observed and recorded about conflict situation', 'Conflict analysis', 'Conflict management', 'Conflict inplementation', 'Conflict resolution', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2455, 15, '12 ________ are those men and women group or parties who are directly or indirectly involved in conflict and its outcome', 'Participant', 'Stakeholder', 'Benefactors', 'Undertaken', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2456, 15, '13 All these are cartegories of stakeholders except ______', 'Tertiary', 'Primary', 'Secondary', 'Interested', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2457, 15, '14 The criteria for determining stakeholders include all the following except __________', 'Functionality', 'Representativity', 'Moral Authority', 'Civility', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2458, 15, '15 The elements required to structure analysis of stakeholder include the following except', 'Relationship', 'Agenda', 'Priorities', 'Needs', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2459, 15, '16 For a conflict analyst all the following are essentials except ________', 'History of the conflict', 'Context of the conflict', 'Power relations', 'Intention', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2460, 15, '17 There are two major types of power that can be exercised during conflict. They are _________________', 'Up and down power', 'Soft and hard power', 'High and low power', 'Positive and negative power', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2461, 15, '18 The party that often hide their identities during conflict situation but supply primary party is called ________', 'Passive party', 'Concerned party', 'Supporting party', 'Shadow party', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2462, 15, '19 One of the following is not part of the pre-intervertion conflict analysis _____________', 'Timing', 'Issues', 'Stages of conflict', 'Decision making', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2463, 15, '20 For conflict management practitioners to have a clear picture of issues he must use one of the following analytical tools __________', 'Conflict philosopy and metaphysic', 'Inter and intra personal skill', 'Conflict mapping and Tracking', 'Conflict resources and reflection', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2464, 15, '1 ECOWAS is a', 'Regional organisation', 'Subregional organisation', 'Global organisation', 'Continental organisation', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2465, 15, '2 The Commonwealth of Nation is a voluntary association of former ________ colonies', 'French', 'British', 'French and British', 'All Colonial', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2466, 15, '3 Which member of the Commonwealth in 1961 ceased to be a member because of its apartheid policy?', 'Canada', 'Ireland', 'South Africa', 'Australia', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2467, 15, '4 Which assistance attracts permission from EEC members before Britain offers it to any commonwealth member?', 'Commonwealth games', 'Technical and monetary', 'Military', 'Trade', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2468, 15, '5 Which is not a vestige of commonwealth history on her members?', 'Human right', 'Rule of law', 'Common language', 'Africanism', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2469, 15, '6 Which conflict may be non-resolvable?', 'Conflict over resources', 'Conflict over psychological needs', 'Conflict over values', 'Conflict over inadequate information', 'C', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2470, 15, '7 Conflict management does not include?', 'Conflict limitation', 'Conflict escalation', 'Conflict containment', 'Conflict litigation', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2471, 15, '8 The goal of negotiation (Jeong 2000: 168) is "to ______ agreement through joint decision making between parties', 'Reach', 'Impose', 'Oppose', 'Enforce', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2472, 15, '9 As a principle of conflict management negotiation requires __________', 'Meeting the legitimate interests of the parties to the extent possible', 'Resolving conflicting intererests fairly', 'Durable and preservation of on-going relationships', 'All the options', 'D', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2473, 15, '10 The Acronym ECOWAS is', 'Economic Countries of West African States', 'Economic Communityof West African States', 'Encompassing Countries if West African States', 'Ecomiun of West African Countries', 'B', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
(2474, 15, '11 Which is true of an international organisation?', 'Forum for the pursuit of international peace and security', 'International organisations have the status of a state', 'International organisation do not have arrangements transcending national boundaries', 'Membership is mandatory', 'A', '2016-04-11 21:18:27'),
